node.text: Switch off, settle in… and relax! 🙏 From @southaustralia’s surreal salt lakes to the inviting shores of @queensland’s @visitfraserisland, today we invite you to escape reality and soak up the serenity of our white-hued landscapes instead. Whether it’s a wombat wandering through #MtKosciuszko’s powdery alpine peaks or stunning @sydney harbour views, we’re certain you’ll find peace of mind whilst immersing yourself in the sounds and sights of our country via Australia in 8D.🕊️ Start planning your next relaxing getaway via the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: WHITE: A Moment of Peace - 8D Escapes

node.text: There’s no doubt about it, pink certainly suits Australia 💕 We couldn’t help but spread the love, or should we say, the lovely feeling, that these magical #magenta scenes from across our country invoke. Allow yourself a little time to marvel at the striking hues of @westernaustralia’s pink lake, take in the @visitgreatoceanroad and @australiasnorthwest's candy-coloured #sunset skies and savour the serenity of @tropicalnorthqueensland, as you fall head over heels with Australia in 8D 😍 To experience dreamy pastel-hued moments like this for yourself, head to the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: MAGENTA: A Moment of Freedom - 8D Escapes

node.text: Breathe in, breathe out … your tranquil adventure through our lush landscapes starts here 😌 Inspired by shades of green, today we’re transporting you to some of the most calming and captivating destinations across Australia, from @tropicalnorthqueensland's ancient rainforest and @rottnestislandwa’s quokka-filled shores, to the magnificent @visitbluemountains and ruggedly beautiful @ntaustralia. Sit back and immerse yourself in the raw and rejuvenating sights and sounds of Australia in 8D; we like to think of it as natural therapy, and relaxation is guaranteed 💚. For more inspiration on how to plan your next nature-based getaway, head to the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: GREEN: A Moment of Calm - 8D Escapes

node.text: While we know not everyone is able to travel here at the moment, we encourage you all, wherever you are, to keep dreaming of those bucket list destinations, secret escapes and once-in-a-lifetime experiences Australia has to offer. When it's safe, and the time is right, get out there and explore this big beautiful backyard of ours. #seeaustralia #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Today we’re rolling out Australia’s red carpet, just for you ❤️ Scarlet, cerise, ruby… call it what you like, it’s an unforgettable hue that can be found in abundance along the road less travelled in our big, bold and beautiful backyard. Take in the sights and sounds of the @ntaustralia’s aptly named #RedCentre and be amazed by the @australiasnorthwest #HorizontalFalls, via Australia in 8D. Feeling inspired to plan your own colourful adventure? Head to the link in our bio to discover more of Australia’s striking scenery. #seeaustralia

node.title: RED: A Moment of Escape - 8D Escapes

node.text: If you’re into mystery and thrills, step right this way... 🖤 There’s just something about @visitmelbourne’s sparkling city skyline and the pitter-patter of penguins exploring #PhillipIsland at dusk that leaves you wanting more. Feel the suspense that the patterns, textures and sounds of the @ngvmelbourne invoke, and allow your breath to be taken away by the sheer power of #KakaduNationalPark’s waterfalls in @ntaustralia. Elegant and bold, Australia’s landscapes with a touch of black demand to be seen and explored via Australia in 8D 😎 To create your own adventure inspired by this dark and mystical hue, click the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: Black: A Moment of Inspiration - 8D Escapes

node.text: From wide-open skies to vast expanses of sea, Australia’s many shades of blue are simply irresistible 💙 Today we’re inviting you to dip your toes into our calming oceans, picturesque pools and idyllic island shores. Play with Australian Sea Lions at #BairdBay in @southaustralia, discover the colourful wonders of the @gbrmarinepark, see dolphins surfing the sparkling waves of @AustraliasGoldenOutback, and listen in awe to whales singing in @visitfrasercoast. Now is the time to escape reality and soak up the blissful-blues of Australia in 8D. To discover more holiday ideas inspired by this refreshing hue, click the link in our bio. #seeaustralia

node.title: Blue: A Moment of Joy - 8D Escapes

Hear from @chrishemsworth and find out what these @australianopen tennis stars love about visiting us. 🎾💚 This special message played at the #AustralianOpen in @rodlaverarena this week, as the tournament rebrands as "Australia is Open" during the finals weekend to let everyone know that we are welcoming visitors to take a #HolidayHereThisYear. Each January, this exciting Grand Slam tournament draws #tennis fanatics and spectators from all over the world to @visitmelbourne, it's a must-do for anyone who loves sports, music, food and fun!

#seeaustralia #visitmelbourne #AusOpen #AustraliaisOpen

node.text: When it's been a REALLY long day! 😉😂 The @jettyroadretreat team were lucky to see this seal pup at #NinetyMileBeach in @visitgippsland over the weekend. Just over 4 hours from @visitmelbourne, this 90-mile stretch of golden sand is one of #visitgippsland's most popular natural attractions (and the sweet local wildlife make it even better!) Extend your stay in this beautiful region and book in to one of @jettyroadretreat's four waterfront cabins. #seeaustralia #visitvictoria #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Today we're joining @bonniewhitfield on a paddle around @visitlordhoweisland 🛶 This @visitnsw paradise can be reached in less than two hours by plane from @sydney or @visitbrisbane. It's known as one of the most sustainable destinations in the world – about 75% of the island’s original natural vegetation remains intact and undisturbed, and its beaches, coral reef and marine environment are pristine. Enjoy this haven when travel permits by staying at @capellalodge, @pinetreeslodge, or @arajillaretreat. #seeaustralia #LoveNSW #LordHoweIsland #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on August 30, 2021. May be an image of tree and nature.

node.text: Care to join us for a stroll through the world's oldest rainforest? 🍃 Located in @tropicalnorthqueensland and home to the Kuku Yalanji people, the #DaintreeRainforest is the perfect place to disconnect as you immerse yourself in nature. Hop on the @skyrailcairns, where the journey is just as spectacular as the destination. As this @queensland cableway winds its way from #Cairns to #Kuranda, all you need to do is take in the epic panoramic views! #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #exploreTNQ #theancientrainforest #holidayherethisyear

node.text: It seems @southaustralia has its very own Loch Ness monster 😉 The team at @murrayrivertrails caught this #Emu taking an afternoon dip in the mighty #MurrayRiver, Australia's longest river. You can experience scenery like this for yourself on the #MurrayRiverWalk and Murray River Safari tours with @murrayrivertrails, an awarded eco-tourism operator in the @riverlandsouthaustralia region 🍃 FACT: Emus love the water and are surprisingly good swimmers. Their long, powerful legs allow them to paddle quickly and also reach top speeds of 50km/h on land! #seeaustralia #seesouthaustralia #Riverland #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Your daily meditation starts now 🧘 @elle_fit captured this mesmerising scene from #DoubleIslandPoint in @queensland. This coastal headland sits within the #GreatSandyNationalPark in @visitsunshinecoast. Explore the area by hiking the Double Island Point walk along the high dunes from #RainbowBeach to the point, and be sure to stop for lunch on the headland to take in the incredible sweeping views over the ocean 🌊#seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #visitsunshinecoast #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on August 28, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text: The tour guides sure are cute at #LuckyBay 🙊 @_johnson_maria_ met this curious mum and joey while visiting this popular @westernaustralia beach, where even the roos can't resist lazing on the white sand! Located 40-minutes from @visitesperance, you'll find this dreamy beach within #CapeLeGrandNationalPark in @australiasgoldenoutback. If you decide to extend your stay (we wouldn't blame you), simply pitch your tent at the nearby campground. #seeaustralia #westernaustralia #australiasgoldenoutback #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on August 28, 2021. May be an image of nature and body of water.

node.text: When it comes to hidden gems, there are plenty to be found in @tourismtopend! Let us introduce you to #ButterflyGorge 🦋 Captured here by @joshdlobb, this GORGE-ous oasis is home to the Wagiman people and can be found between @visitkatherine and #Darwin in @ntaustralia. Aptly named, the cool crevices in the rock faces here provide shelter for thousands of Common Crow Butterflies. Accessible by 4WD only, visitors often find they have this little slice of heaven entirely to themselves! #SeeAustralia #NTAustralia #TourismTopEnd #HolidayHereThisYear

node.text: "I've been waiting ALL day for you to come play with me!" 💙 @nikkiki73 and her @kangarooislandodysseys tour got this wonderful welcome from a resident Australian #SeaLion pup at @sealbay. One of the many highlights of visiting @southaustralia's @authentickangarooisland is seeing these creatures in their natural habitat, and winter and spring are perfect times to visit as the sea lions love hanging out in the dunes away from the sea breeze, providing some pretty incredible viewing opportunities! #seeaustralia #seesouthaustralia #KangarooIsland #holidayherethisyear

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia on August 27, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text: Honey, I bought a boat! 😆 Thanks to @keystoadventure and @elle_fit for this stellar shot, captured on a camping trip on Quandamooka Country (South Stradbroke Island) in @queensland's @visitmoretonbayregion. South Straddie, as it's known by locals, has amazing surfing, swimming and bushwalking with loads of native wildlife. We recommend pitching a tent at Tipplers Campground, or North and South Currigee, and fully exploring this @destinationgoldcoast island! #seeaustralia #PlayGoldCoast #VisitMoretonBayRegion #thisisqueensland #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Sometimes you've just got to strut your stuff 😎 @renepaige_ came across these #SharkBay locals as they made their morning commute through this stunning part of @australiascoralcoast. Known to the local Malgana people as Gutharraguda, the sensational Shark Bay #WorldHeritageArea in @westernaustralia is famous for its friendly wildlife, and we're not just talking about the emus! On any visit, you're likely to spot the sociable resident dolphins, manta rays or kangaroos who pop out to say g'day! #seeaustralia #thisiswa #australiascoralcoast #holidayherethisyear

node.text: "Are we there yet?" 😂 We sure are buddy! Welcome to Mundatharrda (#KennedyRangeNationalPark) in @australiasgoldenoutback 😍 Captured here by @drifters_au, the beautiful gorges and red rock landscape of Mundatharrda can be found around 2-hours outside of the coastal town of @carnarvonvisitorcentre in @westernaustralia. For views like this one, book a scenic flight with @coralcoasthelicopterservices. #seeaustralia #thisisWA #goldenoutback #holidayherethisyear

node.text: Having a sleep-in today are we? 👀 @little.gypsies had this early morning visitor pop by to check she was making the most of the glorious day outside 😄 Known for its resident #cockatoos and spectacular views, @hamiltonisland in @whitsundaysqld makes for a pretty special @queensland holiday. Not only are the locals friendly, this island has some truly magical beaches (think white sand, clear blue water and tons of marine life), plus it gives you easy access to the #GreatBarrierReef and #WhitehavenBeach. #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland #lovewhitsundays #holidayherethisyear
